lead_paragraph: Mr. Moïse, who received 55 percent of the vote, said, “If they want to spend money, we are open to that, but we will show you exactly where to spend this.”

byline.contributor: Andre Paultre contributed reporting from Port-au-Prince, Haiti.

headline.print_headline: 20 Months Later, Haiti Has a President
headline.main: President-Elect Jovenel Moïse of Haiti Vows to Create Plan to Channel Aid

snippet: Mr. Moïse, who received 55 percent of the vote, said, “If they want to spend money, we are open to that, but we will show you exactly where to spend this.”...
abstract: Haiti's electoral council announces victory of Jovenel Moise in presidential election, ending almost two-year electoral process bedeviled by accusations of fraud, delays, natural disasters and very low voter turnout.
